Name: acrokeratosis verruciformis
Definition: A keratosis that has_material_basis_in mutations in the ATP2A2 gene.

Name: acquired hyperkeratosis
Definition: A cognitive disorder resulting from a loss of brain function affecting memory

Name: keratosis follicularis
Definition: A skin disease that is characterized by fluid filled blisters.

Name: palmoplantar keratosis
Definition: A keratosis characterized by abnormal thickening of the palms and the soles.

Name: porokeratosis
Definition: A bilirubin metabolic disorder that involves a build up of bilirubin as bilirubin is not being broken down as a result of a lack or deficiency of the enzyme uridine diphosphate glycosyltransferase (UGT).

Name: seborrheic keratosis
Definition: An extraosseous chondrosarcoma that has_material_basis_in cells derived from transformed cells that produce cartilage and is characterized by a marked abundance of extracellular mucoid (myxoid) matrix.

Name: cholesteatoma
Definition: A keratosis characterized by keratinizing squamous epithelium located in middle ear and/or mastoid

Name: obsolete Mycosis fungoides involving lymph nodes of head
Definition: A keratosis characterized by keratinizing squamous epithelium located in middle ear and/or mastoid
Synonym: Mycosis fungoides of the lymph nodes of head
